            			Element Selector
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			The "element" selector selects all instances of a given element. This selector is also called the "tag" or "type" selector as it specifically targets HTML elements of a specific type, thus, element, tag, or type selector. 
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			For Example:<br>
            			p {<br>
