            			Class Selector
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			Selects the HTML elements on the page with the specified class. Since HTML elements can contain multiple classes per element, this is not exclusive like creating an "id" CSS selector.
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			For example:<br>
            			.highlight {<br>
            			....background: yellow;<br>
            			}<br>
            		</div>
            	</div>
            	<div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			Attribute Selector
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			Elements on the page with the specified attribute. For example, the following example applies to img src="image.png"> BUT NOT img> tags.
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			img[src] {<br>
            			....property: value;<br>
            			}<br>
            		</div>
            	</div>
            	<div>	
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			Pseudo-Class Selector
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			Applies to the specified HTML elements only when in the specified state. For example, "a:hover" means that the CSS will apply to the "attribute" HTML element only when the "a" attribute is hovered over the link.
            		</div>
            		<div class="cssSelectors">
            			For example:<br>
            			a:hover {<br>
            			....color: red;<br>
            			}<br>
            		</div>
            	</div>
            </div>
