            	<h2>Colors in CSS</h2>
            	<ul>
            		<li>
            			Hexadecimal Scale
            			<ul>
            				<li>
            					# plus 6 character hexadecimal string identifying a specific color.
            					h1 {<br>
            					....color: #4B0082; <br>
            					}<br>
            				</li>
            			</ul>
            		</li>
            		<li>
            			RGB Scale
            			<ul>
            				<li>
            					3 channels: red, green, and blue. Each ranges from 0-255. For example:<br>
            					h1 {<br>
            					....color: rgb(11,99,150);<br>
            					}<br>
            				</li>
            			</ul>
            		</li>
            		<li>
            			RGBA Scale
            			<ul>
            				<li>
            					Just like the RGB scale except RGBA has a 4th, "alpha" channel: transparency. This channel ranges from .0-1.0 <br>
            					h1 {<br>
            					....color: rgba (11, 99, 150, 1);<br>
            					}<br>
            					<br>
            					<!-- Opacity of 1 means that the color is full strength -->
            
            					h3 {<br>
            					....color: rgba (11, 99, 150, .6);<br>
            					}<br>
            					<!-- Opacity of .6 removes 40% of the color thus spreading 60% of it accros 100% of the surface area thus diffusing the color -->
            
            					h1 {<br>
            					....color: rgba (11, 99, 150, .2);<br>
            					}<br>
            					<!-- Opacity of .2 means that only 20% of the full strength color is diffused over 100% of the image, thus reducing the amount of color that can be seen by 80%. -->
            				</li>
            			</ul>
            		</li>
            		<li>
            			Color and Background
            			<ul>
            				<li>
            					Use "color" to set text color, and "background" to set the color of the background of whatever HTML element has been selected (especially salient for div's). Ex: <br>
